message.content: cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.EDU. The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques to assess the difficulty and discrimination of multiple-choice questions. This falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as information retrieval (cs.IR) since the model is trained on a large-scale dataset from an e-learning platform. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the model in the context of education (cs.EDU). Finally, the paper's focus on NLP techniques and their application to educational assessment makes it likely to be categorized under the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG).
